The lawyers presented plenty of evidence to put Amber Heard's character and credibility into question (making her an unreliable witness), which the judge bizarrely chose to ignore. He said despite the evidence (other witness accounts, documentation from doctors, audio confessions, dated photographs, etc) conflicting with Heard's accounts of abuse on the stand, he believed what she said on the stand. He didn't, however, believe what other witnesses said under oath, if they were in favor of Depp or their testimony clashed with Heard's testimony.. For the judge to push aside a great deal of evidence and testimony that dispute Amber's account and STILL decide that she's to be believed because of what she said on the stand, then he's a fool. It's outrageous. It was his job to determine if Heard was a credible witness - he "found" that she was, based on... well.. lol.. we still don't know for sure?! Even without the now 100% proven lie about charity donations, there was enough presented in UK court to conclude that Amber was untruthful and unreliable and her (perjurious) testimony on the stand shouldn't have been given ALL of the weight.. Justice Nicol and his "findings" are a sham.

It's called a "conflict of interest." A judge can have a connection to one side or the other, the point is he/she is supposed to DISCLOSE it and allow the parties in the suit the opportunity to request another judge if they feel the judge would be biased. Consider a judge in a small town, he knows everyone personally, they all know he knows the other side personally, does that mean the judge can't rule fair? BUT if the judge disclosed that he owned stock in common with party A's company, yeah, party B should have that fact disclosed to them, that might bare on the facts in the case. The fact that the judge hid the fact of his familial connection to members of the Sun's team, that's VERY telling, Depp's team should have known that pre-trial, the judge was ethically REQUIRED to disclose that and didn't.
